# Features

## 1. Card Composer

| Element | Details |
|---|---|
| Salutation | Optional freeform text field. Placeholder: `"dear my little duck prince,"` |
| Note body | Short-form text. Suggested max ~150 chars to preserve the card feel. |
| Valediction | Optional freeform. Placeholder: `"– your little ketchup packet"` |

All text fields should feel like writing on stationery — appropriate fonts per card style, no sterile input boxes.

---

## 2. Card Styles

A curated set of card themes. Each has its own:

- Background (color, texture, pattern)
- Border/frame treatment
- Font pairing
- Default particle animation

### Initial Set of 6 Styles

| Style Name | Vibe | Colors | Fonts | Default Animation |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| Grid Garden | Sweet, pastel, stationery | Mint, soft blue, gold | Itim + Jersey 15 | Stars |
| Duck Pond | Quirky, illustrative, bold | Cobalt blue, white | Kurale + Itim | Confetti |
| Sakura Cloud | Romantic, soft, airy | Blush, sage, white | Kurale + serif | Cherry blossoms |
| Starfire | Dreamy, dark, celestial | Midnight, rose gold, cream | Jersey 15 + thin serif | Falling stars |
| Cottagecore | Warm, earthy, whimsical | Warm cream, rust, sage | Itim + handwritten | Leaves |
| Y2K Candy | Bold, chaotic, fun | Hot pink, lime, sky | Jersey 15 + bold display | Rainbow confetti |

Each card style ships with a default decorative illustration or motif (e.g. ducks, cats, flowers, stars) placed decoratively — not user-controlled, just part of the charm.

---

## 3. Animation Effects (Particles)

Sender picks one overlay animation that plays when the card is open:

- ❄️ Snow
- ⭐ Stars (twinkling)
- 🌸 Cherry blossoms
- 🎊 Rainbow confetti
- 🔥 Fireflies (soft, not intense fire)
- 🍃 Floating leaves
- 💫 Sparkles
- 🫧 Bubbles

Animations should feel like Partiful — ambient, looping, delightful. Not in-your-face.

---

## 4. Preview Mode

Before sending, sender sees a real-time preview of:

- The card with their text
- The animation playing
- How it'll look on mobile (since receiver likely opens on phone)

---

## 5. Envelope Experience (Receiver View)

This is the magic moment — the thing that makes it feel like mail.

### Receiver Flow

1. Receiver opens the link → sees a sealed envelope (styled to match the card vibe)
2. A small prompt appears: `"You've got a note 💌"`
3. Tap/click → envelope opens with a satisfying animation (flap lifts, card slides out)
4. Card is revealed with its particle animation playing
5. Card is static (no editing, no reply flow in v1)

The envelope should match the card style's color palette.

---

## 6. Sharing

- Sending generates a unique URL (e.g. `CuteNotes.app/n/abc123`)
- Sender can copy link or share directly via iMessage, Instagram DMs, etc.
- No login required for either party in v1

---

# Out of Scope (v1)

- User accounts / note history
- Two-way replies
- Custom illustrations or image uploads
- Push/SMS/email delivery (link sharing only)
- Mobile app (web-first)
- Audio or sound effects

---

# Design Principles

### The card is the product
Every design decision should serve the emotional impact of the card itself — not UI chrome.

### Whimsy has craft
Cute doesn't mean sloppy. Animations should feel considered, not chaotic.

### Speed of delight
Sender should be able to go from open to sent in under 2 minutes.

### Receiver-first magic
The envelope reveal is the hero moment. Invest in it.

---

# Success Metrics (v1)

| Metric | Goal |
|---|---|
| Time to send (first note) | < 2 min |
| Envelope open rate | > 80% of links opened |
| Card styles used | Distribution across ≥ 3 styles |
| Qualitative | “This is so cute” reactions from receivers |

---

# Open Questions

- **Expiration:** Should notes expire, or live forever? Forever feels more special but has cost implications.
- **Font loading:** Web fonts add latency — how do we make the composer feel instant?
- **Animation performance:** Particle effects on low-end phones — need a graceful fallback.
- **Reply hook:** Even in v1, should there be a subtle “send one back?” CTA to grow organically?

